The paper presents a chess engine that uses deep reinforcement learning to learn its evaluation function and improve its gameplay through self-play. This involves automatic feature extraction and pattern recognition, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and game theory (cs.GT).
